  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What advice do you have for a seventeen year old who is pretty confused in life?",
  "response": "Feeling confused at seventeen is completely normal\u2014many people your age are grappling with big questions about identity, future plans, and relationships. Here are a few pieces of advice that might help:\n\n1. **Explore Interests**: Take the time to explore different hobbies, subjects, and activities. This could help you discover what you are truly passionate about and where your strengths lie.\n\n2. **Set Small Goals**: Break down your larger ambitions into smaller, manageable goals. This makes it easier to track progress and not feel overwhelmed.\n\n3. **Talk It Out**: Don\u2019t hesitate to talk to trusted friends, family members, or mentors about your feelings. They can provide valuable perspectives and support.\n\n4. **Try New Things**: Be open to trying new experiences, whether that\u2019s joining a club, volunteering, or taking a class outside your comfort zone. New experiences can provide clarity and confidence.\n\n5. **Practice Self-Reflection**: Spend some time reflecting on your values, beliefs, and experiences. Journaling can be a helpful tool for this. Understanding yourself better can guide your decisions.\n\n6. **Stay Open-Minded**: Life is full of possibilities, and paths may change. Be adaptable and open to new directions.\n\n7. **Limit Comparisons**: It\u2019s easy to look at peers and feel behind or lost. Remember, everyone has their own journey. Focus on your own growth and progress.\n\n8. **Seek Guidance**: Consider talking to a school counselor or a life coach. They can help you explore your feelings and provide guidance.\n\n9. **Focus on Mental Health**: Prioritize your mental well-being. Practice self-care and don\u2019t hesitate to seek help if you\u2019re feeling overwhelmed or anxious.\n\n10. **Trust the Process**: Understand that it\u2019s okay not to have everything figured out. Life is a journey, and it\u2019s perfectly fine to take your time to find your path.\n\nRemember, confusion can be a stepping stone to clarity. Allow yourself the grace to navigate this stage of your life.",
